\cf2 \cb3 Your web server is now running. Point your browser to\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://localhost:1930/"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \ul \ulc6 localhost:1930}}. You should see the assignment page. This confirms that your environment is all set up! (You might briefly see an error message on the page while it loads the JavaScript. The error should disappear quickly; if it persists, follow the instructions on screen to try to identify the issue.)\cb1 \
\
\cb3 Directory structure of the starter files:\'a0\cb1 \
\cb3 Here\'92s a quick overview of the files and folders in the\'a0assign0\'a0directory. This will largely be the same for other assignments.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0\cf2 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
lib:\'a0Contains code that is provided. You will not have to modify any files in this folder.\cb1 \
\ls3\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
package.json:\'a0Defines information about the project, such as its dependencies. You won\'92t have to manually edit this file. For your final project, you may add dependencies using\'a0npm, and these will be added to\'a0package.json\'a0automatically.\cb1 \
\ls3\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
public:\'a0Contains the files served to your browser by the web server. For the first part of the course, all of the files you will edit will be in this folder. This assignment contains two files,\'a0index.html\'a0(which you won\'92t have to edit) and\'a0survey.js\'a0(where you will fill in your answers).\cb1 \
\ls3\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
server.js:\'a0The code to run the web server. You won\'92t have to edit this until we start working on server-side JavaScript, later in the course.\cb1 \
\ls3\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
node_modules\'a0and\'a0package-lock.json:\'a0These don\'92t exist at first, but are created when you first run\'a0
\f1\b npm install
\f0\b0 . They contain the dependencies themselves and information about what was installed. You neither will need to nor should you edit them. It is safe to delete them and rerun\'a0
\f1\b npm install
